Nice off the beaten tourist path place to eat.  It's in a nice little square with trees that my children would love to play on.  Next time kids.- The dinner salad was fruity and nutty and a good starter- The baby squid were simply amazing.  Tender and full of hearty flavor- My wife's salty cod tomato rice was rich, creamy, and delicious- My fish prepared in a suquet sauce was succulent and savory.  Mixing it with the potatoes was perfect- Service was perfect
